        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Limiting Emergency Powers Act of 2021</b></p> <p>This bill provides that a national emergency declared by the President terminates 30 days after a declaration unless a joint resolution affirming such declaration is enacted.</p> <p> All existing emergency declarations expire after two years unless the President requests a renewal that receives congressional approval. </p>]]>
        </text>
